Let R be a ring, let M be a module over R, let R^{n} be the finite-rank free module over R. Then
\mathop {\textrm {Hom}}\nolimits _{R}(R^{n},M)\cong  M^{\oplus  n}
where M^{\oplus  n}=\bigoplus ^{n}_{i=1} M=M\oplus  M\oplus …\oplus  M is just the direct sum of n copies of M.

We see \mathop {	extrm {Hom}}
olimits _{R}(R^{n},M)\cong (\mathop {	extrm {Hom}}
olimits _{R}(R,M))^{n} and \mathop {	extrm {Hom}}
olimits _{R}(R,M)\cong M. The result follows immediately.

Let R be a ring. Then for any m,n\in \mathbb {N}, the following all hold:

